net.sf.sprockets.content

Class CursorWrapperLoader<D extends Cursor>

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.content.Loader<D>
      • android.content.AsyncTaskLoader<D>
        • net.sf.sprockets.content.CursorWrapperLoader<D>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    EasyCursorLoader, ReadCursorLoader

    public abstract class CursorWrapperLoader<D extends Cursor>
extends AsyncTaskLoader<D>
    A loader that queries the ContentResolver and returns a wrapped Cursor. This class implements the Loader protocol in a standard way for querying cursors, building on AsyncTaskLoader to perform the cursor query on a background thread so that it does not block the application's UI.

    A CursorWrapperLoader must be built with the full information for the query to perform, either through the CursorWrapperLoader(Context, Uri, String[], String, String[], String) or creating an empty instance with CursorWrapperLoader(Context) and filling in the desired parameters with setUri(Uri), setSelection(String), setSelectionArgs(String[]), setSortOrder(String), and setProjection(String[]).
